children.text: The load from the upper roof has not been transferred through the floor frame.
The relevant Australian Standard, AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, clause 6.3.3 Bottom Plates states that

‘Where bottom plates supports studs supporting concentrated loads, posts or jamb studs, the plates shall be supported over a floor joist, solid blocking between bottom plate and bearer or concrete slab’ .
These blocks must be installed to properly transfer the roof load through to the slab.
